FBIS4-34559 "drlat120_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Restrictions on Foreign Journalists Announced Restrictions on Foreign Journalists Announced PA2206045694 Paris AFP in Spanish 0407 GMT 21 Jun 94 PA2206045694 Paris AFP Spanish BFN [Text] Port-au-Prince, 21 Jun (AFP) -- Tuesday night, the Ministry of Information, Coordination, and Culture announced that hereafter foreign journalists must "request and obtain" from that Ministry authorization to go to the cities in the provinces. The objective of the measure is "to guarantee the security of foreign journalists in the country," the communique notes. Many foreign journalists, including the crews of the principal U.S. television stations, are in Port-au-Prince just as the new U.S. sanctions are to be enforced.
